                        <part>The Virginians</part>
                     </title>. On the preliminary two fly-leaves Thackeray has written his name and address, "36 Onslow Square, Brompton." The final leaf of the volume has an unfinished verse of poetry and a pencil sketch of Pocahontas rescuing Captain John Smith. On page 14 Thackeray transcribed a letter of his to Messrs. Sampson, Low &amp; Son, referring to <title localtype="simple" render="italic">
                        <part>The Virginians</part>
                     </title>, dated December 11, 1857. With an armorial bookplate of John and Dorothea Castles.</p>
